00:16.065 --> 00:18.201
Grabbed your paper.

00:18.269 --> 00:20.803
You ready to get started
with this?

00:21.839 --> 00:23.673
Do I have a choice?

00:23.741 --> 00:26.342
Your ten day window
is up, Clark.

00:26.410 --> 00:27.977
You know how it is.

00:28.045 --> 00:30.780
You don't comply with the law,
I got to tell the judge.

00:30.848 --> 00:32.815
Now come on.

00:32.883 --> 00:34.901
Let's go introduce you
to the neighbors.

00:37.454 --> 00:40.924
I just don't see how
this does anyone any good.

00:40.991 --> 00:42.575
The law's the law, Clark.

00:42.660 --> 00:44.393
You got to do this.

00:44.445 --> 00:46.746
And as your parole officer,
I got to watch you.

00:46.830 --> 00:48.264
I served my time, John.

00:48.332 --> 00:49.899
I just want to
live in peace.

00:49.967 --> 00:51.334
Your new neighbors
have every right

00:51.402 --> 00:53.236
to know who's
moving in next door.

00:53.304 --> 00:56.339
And hey, you ask me,
a little embarrassment's

00:56.406 --> 00:59.175
not a bad price to pay
for getting out of jail.

01:07.417 --> 01:09.585
And you still think
this is a good thing?

01:09.637 --> 01:11.955
I think you got to do
what you got to do.

01:12.022 --> 01:16.025
And right now, you got to
finish putting up these flyers.

01:19.446 --> 01:21.064
Hi, sweetheart.

01:21.131 --> 01:23.533
Morning.

01:37.014 --> 01:39.448
Did you just bring
that paper in?

01:39.500 --> 01:41.150
Yeah, a minute ago. Why?

01:41.218 --> 01:42.285
You want it?

01:42.336 --> 01:44.621
No. Did you talk
to anybody out there?

01:44.688 --> 01:46.522
A man with a tie maybe?

01:46.590 --> 01:49.759
Yeah. He and his friend
were putting up flyers.

01:49.827 --> 01:52.595
I think they're having
a garage sale or something.

02:05.042 --> 02:07.910
Good morning.

